
// The [if] slot in Hyperlambda evaluates a condition and executes its [.lambda] child if the condition is true. The [eq] slot checks if the value of the node referenced by its expression (SOME_EXPRESSION) equals a specified value (SOME_VALUE). If true, the [.lambda] block is executed.
if
   eq:x:@SOME_EXPRESSION
      .:SOME_VALUE
   .lambda
